HEADWORD: Myrcia
<hw>Myr"ci*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A large genus of tropical American trees and
shrubs, nearly related to the true myrtles (<gen>Myrtus</gen>), from
which they differ in having very few seeds in each berry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

